BIB                 12         30
TITLE      Measurements of interaction cross sections for 22-35Na
           isotopes
AUTHOR     (S.Suzuki, M.Takechi, T.Ohtsubo, D.Nishimura, M.Fukuda,
            T.Kuboki, M.Nagashima, T.Suzuki, T.Yamaguchi, A.Ozawa,
            H.Ohishi, T.Moriguchi, T.Sumikama, H.Geissel, N.Aoi,
            R.J.Chen, D.Q.Fang, N.Fukuda, S.Fukuoka, H.Furuki,
            N.Inabe, Y.Ishibashi, T.Ito, T.Izumikawa, D.Kameda,
            T.Kubo, M.Lantz, C.S.Lee, Y.G.Ma, M.Mihara, S.Momota,
            D.Nagae, R.Nishikiori, T.Niwa, T.Ohnishi, K.Okumura,
            T.Ogura, H.Sakurai, K.Sato, Y.Shimbara, H.Suzuki,
            H.Takeda, S.Takeuchi, K.Tanaka, H.Uenishi, M.Winkler,
            Y.Yanagisawa)
INSTITUTE  (2JPNNII,2GERGSI,2JPNSUT,2JPNOSA,2JPNSUU,2JPNTSU,
           2JPNIPC,3CPRNRS,2JPNKUT)
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/CS,66,03084,2014)
           Main reference. See also TITLE and AUTHOR.
           (J,APP/B,42,765,2011) Preliminary data
INC-SOURCE (FRAGM) Secondary beams of 22-35Na were produced via
                   projectile fragmentation of a primary beam of
                   345-MeV/nucleon 48Ca on Be production targets.
SAMPLE     - Chemical-form of target is element.
           - Physical-form of target is solid.
           - Target-thickness is 3.60,1.80 mg/cm2.
METHOD     (TOFDE)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2JPNIPC)
DETECTOR   (MAGSP,PPAC,SCIN,IOCH)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information on source of uncertainties
STATUS     (TABLE,,S.Suzuki+,J,EPJ/CS,66,03084,2014) Figure 2
HISTORY    (20260128R) Received from Dr. M. Takechi.
           (20260129C) MA
